<TEXT>
a federal appeals court friday overturned a 
judges ruling that a virginia savings and loan pay penthouse 
international boardwalk properties inc nearly 130 million for 
allegedly sabotaging a loan 
the decision released friday also overturned an order that 
dominion federal savings and loan association pay 765 million in 
damages to queens city savings and loan the lead lender in a 97 
million loan package for an atlantic city casinohotel project 
penthouse president robert guccione spent more than 60 million 
on the casino project but sought extra financing in 1983 dominion 
federal promised to provide 35 million in funding although it was 
barred by law from making a single loan of more than 185 million 
us district judge kevin duffy accused dominion chairman 
william walde in a july 31 1987 decision of launching a coverup 
after a third lender pulled out of the deal 
the appeals court however said in its 67page opinion there 
was no evidence establishing that dominion intended not to proceed 
and there is an abundance of evidence to indicate just the 
opposite 
dominion federal announced the 2nd us circuit court of appeals 
decision reporters could not obtain copies late friday 
the mclean vabased lending institution had posted a 50 
million bond while awaiting the appeal 
</TEXT>
