ceasefire to test irans intentions iran refused and both sides 
agreed on direct talks shortly after the halt in hostilities 
i am sure the parties sincerely want to solve the problem 
perez de cuellar said today but i think we have to be a little 
patient 
he said the arrangement was made at the request of the two 
countries i would prefer to have them all the time in the main 
room with me but he said i have to accommodate myself to the 
wish of the parties 
the talks began about one hour late velayati declined to answer 
questions from reporters at the entrance of the building the bulk 
of the iranian delegation had arrived earlier on time for the 
meeting 
giuliani denied reports by un officials that the 
secretarygeneral was considering appointing former swiss president 
kurt furgler as his special representative to continue the 
iraniraq talks 
he also dismissed a swiss radio report that edouard brunner the 
no 2 in the swiss foreign ministry would be appointed he said if 
brunner is appointed swiss ambassador to washington there is no 
question of the secretarygeneral appointing him as his personal 
representative giuliani said 
brunner is being considered for the post but if appointed he 
would not take the position until next year 
the peace process is expected to be long and difficult possibly 
lasting years the direct talks were made possible after iran and 
iraq both accepted un security council resolution 598 calling 
for a ceasefire 
before the talks began perez de cuellar held several meetings 
with aziz and velayati in new york the warring sides agreed to 
hold direct talks following a ceasefire that began aug 20 
the truce appeared to be holding saeem fahmawi a spokesman for 
the 350 un observers monitoring the 733mile iraqiran warfront 
said in baghdad there have been no major violations 
the iranian and iraqi delegations in geneva include political 
figures military representatives and legal experts on war relief 
prisoner repatriation and reparations 
the agenda was not disclosed but the secretarygeneral said the 
talks were aimed at carrying out the ceasefire resolution which 
also calls for troop withdrawal to international boundaries return 
of war prisoners reparations and a comprehensive peace 
it also calls for an impartial body to determine which side 
started the war 
