you just need a good instructor 
the blind sailors sail every saturday either at the courageous 
sailing center at the charlestown navy yard or in the protected 
waters of pleasure bay off castle island in south boston 
at the end of the summer they participate in a special regatta 
the rules are simple one sighted volunteer accompanies each blind 
sailor in a boat but the volunteer is not allowed to touch anything 
during the race he or she is allowed only to warn of hazards 
this isnt going to make them to be olympic sailors said 
mcdonough were just teaching them something to love that they 
otherwise would never get a chance to do 
