the thursday night incident came as the army was poised to cut 
the required tour length in panama part of a continuing effort to 
reduce the number of military dependents in the troubled central 
american nation 
the service hopes to encourage more soldiers to opt for 
socalled unaccompanied tours leaving their families behind 
by reducing the tour commitment said defense officials who asked 
not to be named 
