at brunswick ga but rain elsewhere was lighter 
during the night a severe storm spun off high wind that ripped 
out windows and walls and cut power at the southern california town 
of baker in the mojave desert 
no injuries were reported but several mobile homes were damaged 
windows at numerous businesses were blown out and the back wall of 
an auto service garage was knocked down collapsing its roof said 
baker firefighter james meral 
officials estimated damage at 500000 to 1 million there was 
no official reading on wind speed in the town 150 miles northeast 
of los angeles 
