delivery of west texas intermediate the benchmark grade of us 
crude oil fell 37 cents a barrel to close at 1531 thursday 
october crude closed 2 cents lower in wednesdays trading 
contracts for september delivery of wholesale unleaded gasoline 
dropped 107 cents to finish at 4644 cents a gallon most other 
contract months for gasoline also declined wholesale heating oil 
for september fell 130 cents to 4245 cents a gallon 
analysts said the october contract for crude oil tumbled below a 
critical technical level of 1550 a barrel on reports that 
production by the organization of petroleum exporting countries had 
surged anew 
reports that opec production has reached 195 million to 20 
million barrels a day caused a sharp decline in the market today 
said chris mccormack an analyst with drexel burnham lambert inc 
the market also broke a key technical level 
analysts said that once the market hit 1550 a barrel negative 
sentiment took over sending prices even lower 
the oil futures market has been largely inactive in recent 
weeks without much fresh news on supply and demand to guide it 
analysts said thursdays reports provided the first sign of 
direction in some time and speculated that prices could weaken 
further as the increased oil outflow reaches consuming nations 
it looks like were about to start a move to the down side 
mccormack said 
last week the market focused on developments in the middle east 
and a tentative ceasefire between iran and iraq analysts have 
speculated that an end to the fighting between the two opec nations 
could mean the fractious 13member oil cartel would set production 
limits thus helping to raise world oil prices 
