horses sara shaw is busy running a mailorder food business out of 
her farm house that ships smoked pheasant and other locally 
produced foods all over the country 
shaw who was involved in the antiwar movement in the 1960s and 
worked as a book designer in new york city before moving to 
minnesota in 1973 started prairie gourmet last summer 
i dont envision myself as the head of a big corporation 
said shaw whose business is located near ortonville in western 
minnesota i just want it to be a stable business that offers 
employment to people in the area 
